profile_short_name:Catimor NAT Yunnan v3
profile_designer:Claude
profile_description:Yunnan Pu'er Catimor Natural 1650m\vMoisture: 11.5% | Density: 759g/L\vLoad: 120g (standard batch)\v\vVersion 3 - Scaled to 120g based on V1/V2 60g data\v\vKey learnings from V1/V2 (60g):\v- FC confirmed at ~193-194C (two roasts consistent)\v- Floral/fruit aroma is the dominant character\v- ROR stays positive with Kd=3.10 (excellent stability)\v- V1: 8% weight loss (underdeveloped), V2: 8.7% (still low)\v- Mid-section profile lag was curve slope issue, not power\v- Tail bitterness likely Catimor varietal trait\v\vV3 changes (60g -> 120g scaling):\v1. reference_load_size: 60 -> 120 (standard batch)\v2. preheat: 770W -> 810W (120g needs more thermal energy,\v   but Catimor low density 759 heats faster than Catuai 829,\v   so lower than Catuai V6's 830W)\v3. Fan profile: 14200 -> 14700 base (120g standard airflow)\v4. Curve times extended: 120g has 2x thermal mass\v5. Mid-section slope gentler than V2 (V2 lesson: reduce\v   PID chasing pressure)\v6. Endpoint: 390s/206C for more development\v   (target weight loss 11-13%)\v\vRecommended Levels:\v  Nordic Light: Level 1.0 (~198C)\v  Light Filter: Level 1.5 (~200C)\v  Sweet Balanced: Level 2.0 (~202C)\v  Full Body: Level 2.5 (~204C)\v\vTarget: Level 2.0 (202C)\vExpected total time: 6:20-6:50\vExpected weight loss: 11-13%\vExpected dev ratio: 16-20%\v\vSafety: No zone boosts, standard end_ratio/min_ROR.\v
